metadata.title: Cessna 210 Centurion
aws::graph::propositions: Cessna 210 Centurion Model Variants
The C210N model had gear doors removed due to extensive maintenance and handling problems.
Most early Cessna 210 Centurion models had gear doors removed.
The removal of gear doors left early models similar to the "N" model.
The C210N was produced from 1979 to 1985.
1943 C210N aircraft were built.
The 210R Centurion was a 210N with longer-span stabilizers.
The 210R Centurion had minor changes from the 210N.
The 210R Centurion was produced in 1986.
112 210R Centurion aircraft were built.
The Turbo Centurion was a variant of the 210R Centurion.
The P210N Pressurized Centurion was a Turbo 210N with a pressurized cabin.
The P210N Pressurized Centurion had four windows on each side.
The P210N Pressurized Centurion had a 310 hp Continental TSIO-520-AF engine.
The Continental TSIO-520-AF engine produced 231 kW of power.
The P210N Pressurized Centurion was produced from 1978 to 1985.
834 P210N Pressurized Centurion aircraft were built.
The P210R Pressurized Centurion was a P210N with longer-span stabilizers.
The P210R Pressurized Centurion had increased takeoff weight compared to the P210N.
The P210R Pressurized Centurion had a 325 hp Continental TSIO-520-CE engine.
The Continental TSIO-520-CE engine produced 242 kW of power.
The P210R Pressurized Centurion was produced in 1986.
40 P210R Pressurized Centurion aircraft were built.

text:
Although this change appeared only on the C210N, most early models have had gear doors removed due to extensive maintenance and handling problems, leaving them similar to the "N". Production years 1979-1985, 1943 built.
210R Centurion / Turbo Centurion
A 210N with longer-span stabilizers and minor changes, production year 1986, 112 built.
P210N Pressurized Centurion
A Turbo 210N with pressurized cabin, four windows each side, with a 310 hp (231 kW) Continental TSIO-520-AF engine, production years 19781985, 834 built.
P210R Pressurized Centurion
A P210N with longer-span stabilizers, increased takeoff weight and a 325 hp (242 kW) Continental TSIO-520-CE engine, production year 1986, 40 built.
